paragraphs.text:
%md
## Selecting a wine that is likley to be good but is inexpensive!
### We've all been there.   We are invited to a party and want to bring something to contribute.   A bottle of wine is always a good option.   But which one?   There are so many!   And we don't want to break the bank for our party gift.   

### Let's try to use the Autonomous Database and Oracle Machine Learning to find a likely tasty and likley to be rated greater than 90 Points (GT_90_Points) adult beverage that is also affordable (Hopefully under $20!).  

Created and last updated April 2020 by: Charlie Berger, Dhvani Sheth, Siddesh Ujjni

Selecting a wine that is likley to be good but is inexpensive!

We've all been there. We are invited to a party and want to bring something to contribute. A bottle of wine is always a good option. But which one? There are so many! And we don't want to break the bank for our party gift.

Let's try to use the Autonomous Database and Oracle Machine Learning to find a likely tasty and likley to be rated greater than 90 Points (GT_90_Points) adult beverage that is also affordable (Hopefully under $20!).

Created and last updated April 2020 by: Charlie Berger, Dhvani Sheth, Siddesh Ujjni

paragraphs.title: Process Steps
paragraphs.text:
%md
#### 1. DATA UNDERSTANDING to explore the data
#### 2. DATA PREPARATION to define the target attribute (GT_90_Points vs. LT_90_Points)
#### 3. MODEL BUILDING to find the key attributes that most influence GT_90_Points_Bin)
#### 4. MODEL BUILDING to build models to predict likley delicious (GT_90_Points_Bin) bottles of wine to buy
#### 5. MODEL DEPLOYMENT by leaving our insights and predictions in the Database to further investigage our wine findings using APEX and/or Oracle Analytics Cloud

#### Note:  Original data comes from Kaggle WineReviews130K data = 130k wine reviews with variety, location, winery, price, and description etc.   Wine Reviews and Twitter Handle were removed.   Points was binned to GT_90 and LT_90 <https://www.kaggle.com/zynicide/wine-reviews>

msg.data:
1. DATA UNDERSTANDING to explore the data

2. DATA PREPARATION to define the target attribute (GT_90_Points vs. LT_90_Points)

3. MODEL BUILDING to find the key attributes that most influence GT_90_Points_Bin)

4. MODEL BUILDING to build models to predict likley delicious (GT_90_Points_Bin) bottles of wine to buy

5. MODEL DEPLOYMENT by leaving our insights and predictions in the Database to further investigage our wine findings using APEX and/or Oracle Analytics Cloud

Note: Original data comes from Kaggle WineReviews130K data = 130k wine reviews with variety, location, winery, price, and description etc. Wine Reviews and Twitter Handle were removed. Points was binned to GT_90 and LT_90 https://www.kaggle.com/zynicide/wine-reviews

paragraphs.title: Create a cumulative gains table
Compare the models
paragraphs.text:
%sql

SELECT A.ALGO_NAME, A.QUANTILE_NUMBER, ROUND(A.GAIN_CUMULATIVE*100,2) GAIN_CUMULATIVE, B.RANDOM_GUESS
FROM ALL_LIFT_DATA A

paragraphs.title: Create table WINEPREDICTIONS of wines less than $15 wines that are predicted to be good wines (GT_90_POINTS)
paragraphs.text:
%sql

CREATE TABLE WINEPREDICTIONS AS 
  SELECT ID, PRICE, COUNTRY, WINERY, REGION_1, DESIGNATION, PROVINCE, VARIETY, PROBABILITY
  FROM (SELECT ID, PRICE, COUNTRY, WINERY, REGION_1, DESIGNATION, PROVINCE, VARIETY,
               PREDICTION_PROBABILITY(WINE_CLASS_MODEL_SVM, 'GT_90_POINTS' USING *) PROBABILITY
          FROM WINEREVIEWS130KTARGET
          WHERE PRICE < 15) 
ORDER BY PROBABILITY DESC;
